		{
			"name": "reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNCMGNiOFNBEAE",
			"relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 года назад",
			"rating": 1,
			"text": {
				"text": "On a first visit it was revealed to me that I will need some medication and temporary filling for a week. Okay.\n\nFiling did fell off after 3 days while brushing my teeth. I figured “okay, temporary for 7 days, 3 days passed, stuff happens, whatever”. So I came and got a replacement for next 4 days.\n\nAfter a week it turns out I need temporary filling for a month with different medication. Again, okay.\n\nThis filling lived for a whole 4 days, and at this point it was no longer okay. It was supposed to hold for a month AT LEAST. And it was 4 days. It also happened at around 19:00 at Friday. You may notice that dentist office is working till 21:00 but it was simple closed - no lights and no one in the office.\n\nI was told by doctor to just take some painkillers and come tomorrow at 10am.\n\nAt this point I was no longer willing to give them benefit of the doubt and just get to a different dentist who was kind enough to take me in in 19:30 at Friday night.\n\nIf my experience is any indication I would suggest to avoid this place all together.\n\nOne time is okay, again - stuff happens. But loosing temporary filling twice in a row after days is not okay for me. I ended up needing 4 procedures in 2 weeks instead of just 2.",
				"languageCode": "en"
			},
			"originalText": {
				"text": "On a first visit it was revealed to me that I will need some medication and temporary filling for a week. Okay.\n\nFiling did fell off after 3 days while brushing my teeth. I figured “okay, temporary for 7 days, 3 days passed, stuff happens, whatever”. So I came and got a replacement for next 4 days.\n\nAfter a week it turns out I need temporary filling for a month with different medication. Again, okay.\n\nThis filling lived for a whole 4 days, and at this point it was no longer okay. It was supposed to hold for a month AT LEAST. And it was 4 days. It also happened at around 19:00 at Friday. You may notice that dentist office is working till 21:00 but it was simple closed - no lights and no one in the office.\n\nI was told by doctor to just take some painkillers and come tomorrow at 10am.\n\nAt this point I was no longer willing to give them benefit of the doubt and just get to a different dentist who was kind enough to take me in in 19:30 at Friday night.\n\nIf my experience is any indication I would suggest to avoid this place all together.\n\nOne time is okay, again - stuff happens. But loosing temporary filling twice in a row after days is not okay for me. I ended up needing 4 procedures in 2 weeks instead of just 2.",
				"languageCode": "en"
			},
